John Lafin

Bio

Im a bench-to-bioinformatics researcher in the Strand Lab at UT Southwestern Medical Center in Dallas, TX. I leverage my background in biomedical research and expertise in single cell and spatial genomics to better understand the biology of the normal human lower urinary tract, informing investigations into diseases like bladder and prostate cancer and BPH. I also develop tools to help democratize single cell data and analysis pipelines.

Education

The University of Iowa | Iowa City, IA

Ph.D.in Free Radical and Radiation Biology | August 2012 - June 2017

The University of Texas at Austin | Austin, TX

B.S. in Biochemistry | August 2007 - May 2011

Experience

UT Southwestern | Resch. Assoc. -> Comp. Biol. | July 2020 - Present

UT Southwestern | Postdoctoral Researcher | July 2017 - July 2020
